Durban - A Chatsworth family lost the upper floor to their home when a fire broke out in their Lenny Naidu Drive residence on Sunday. eThekwini ward 70 councillor Sathasivan Tony Govender said the fire broke on the road level floor just after midday. "The owner said the fire had spread rapidly through the upper floor and consumed the complete top floor of his building. The basement with two rooms were also affected and the lounge suite and the bedding were destroyed in the fire. Two women on the premises were not anywhere near the fire as they were at the granny flat at the rear. They were not affected in any way and they are very safe and free from harms way, "Govender said. To view this video please enable JavaScript, and consider upgrading to a web browser that
